headline: Did Lamb Weston's (LW) New Argentine Facility Just Reshape Its Latin America Growth Story?
summary: Lamb Weston Holdings announced the official opening of its 40,000-square-meter production facility in Mar del Plata, Argentina, which is designed to process up to 200 million pounds of potatoes annually for export to Latin American markets, primarily Brazil. This expansion positions the company to address growing regional demand while strengthening partnerships with over 100 local producers and creating significant employment in the region.
